Object.Field:
This mapping uses Oracle Partition Exchange to perform upload operations for a given partition using the IKM Oracle Partition Exchange.
The mapping REPLACES the existing data of a given partition with the newly source dataset.
The partition exchange operation replaces the entire partition of the partitioned table with the content of the ODI flow table, which only includes the incoming newly dataset from the source tables.
To test this mapping, perform the following steps:
1. Perform a full load of the partitioned table using any of the packages found under the folder "01 - Initial Load Samples". 2. Delete or truncate MY_STG_AREA.ORDERS table. 3. Add new data into the MY_STG_AREA.ORDERS for a given partition, and run this mapping. You can use the INCREMENTAL.SQL script provided in the sample repository zip file to add additional data for a given partition. 4. Once you add additional data for a given partition, execute this mapping. 5. You should see that the mapping replaces the content of the selected partition with the new dataset from the MY_STG_AREA.ORDERS table. The exchange operation replaces the entire partition with the new data set.
This mapping is ideal for partitioned tables where its content can be replaced with new datasets. If the existing data of a given partition cannot be replaced with new datasets, then use the following mapping to perform incremental uploads with Partition Exchange:
Incremental Load - Load By Partition - Flow Control - IKM Oracle Partition Exchange Load - Union Mode
Alternatively, you can use the IKM Oracle Incremental Update to perform update operations and upload data incrementally, but this strategy does not use Oracle Partition Exchange.
Incremental Load - Load By Partition - Flow Control - IKM Oracle Partition Exchange Load - Replace Mode
